-- Yildirim Is Close to Paying $500 Million for 20% of CMA CGM, Echos Says
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-10-14T04:49:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/yildirim-is-close-to-paying-500-million-for-20-of-cma-cgm-echos-says.html
CMA CGM SA is close to an accord
under which Turkish family-owned company Yildirim would pay $500
million for a 20 percent stake, French daily Les Echos reported,
citing unidentified people.  The agreement could be reached as soon as the end of this
week and the payment would be made at the end of November, the
newspaper said. The companies declined to comment, Les Echos
added.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  